            </div>

            <div class="col-12">
                <p>The project “I am Stronger with My Sister” focuses on raising women’s awareness about gender and on strengthening women’s solidarity in the neighborhood and it will systematize all the work the Association has done in the neighborhood since its establishment in 2013 and maintain the local organizational models. The project has been implemented in partnership with Gülsuyu Gülensu Women’s Solidarity House and it has three interacting components.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12 col-xl-8 mx-auto text-center">
                <div class="content-box mor-box">
                    <p class="mt-2">“For the first time in my life, I heard something called ‘stereotype’. I knew what prejudice meant, but I did not know the word ‘stereotype’. In fact, we do discriminate without knowing it.” </p>
                    <p class="bold mb-1">A participant</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12">
                <p class="my-4"><img src="../images/kiz-kardesimle-gucluyum/kiz-kardesimle-gucluyum-4.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt=""></p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-12">
                <p>The first component is called “I am Learning with My Sister”, and it contained trainings and activities organized to increase women’s rights-based awareness in the neighborhood. 90 women from Esenyalı and Gülsuyu neighborhoods completed this training program, which consists of sessions on gender, women’s human rights, violence, legal mechanisms in combating violence, urban rights, media and sexism, body and health. The most pleasing outcome of the training is that the participants have formed a permanent group. There is now a group of sisters in the neighborhood who are curious about their rights and who explore, learn and continue learning by discussing with each other!</p>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-6">
